<subSubSection id="C330CAB17E2BFFE943C0F97D42901A60" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E2BFFE943C0F97D42901A60" blockId="8.[151,1437,1563,1987]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2BFFE943C0F97D42251BF0" bold="true" box="[199,314,1744,1770]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AE2B97E2BFFE9424DF97D412A1BF0" authorityName="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[330,565,1744,1770]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phalerus">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2BFFE9424DF97D412A1BF0" box="[330,565,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Schausiana phalerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AE2B97E2BFFE94071F97D40E81BF0" authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1949" box="[886,1015,1744,1770]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2BFFE94071F97D40E81BF0" box="[886,1015,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Schausiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by (i) the single black dot in the anal area in both 
<specimenCount id="9D2C52B37E2BFFE94280F95842831A15" box="[391,412,1781,1807]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D2C52B37E2BFFE942D3F95842F61A15" box="[468,489,1781,1807]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, (ii) wider spacing of dark brown stripes between veins on the FW postmedial area (especially when compared to its most similar species 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AE2B97E2BFFE941E9F8B540FD1A28" authority="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra, 2020" authorityName="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra" authorityYear="2020" box="[750,994,1816,1842]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalciope" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2BFFE941E9F8B540FD1A28" box="[750,994,1816,1842]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Schausiana chalciope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26DF8537E2BFFE940E0F8B547201A29" box="[999,1087,1816,1843]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2BFFE940E0F8B5471E1A28" bold="true" box="[999,1025,1816,1842]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2BFFE94709F8B547251A28" bold="true" box="[1038,1082,1816,1842]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
), and (iii) the absence of black/ brown markings on the wing margin of the FW and (iv) the absence of black/brown markings at the intersection of the A and CuA 
<subScript id="17AE9B7F7E2BFFE9423AF8DF425A1A9A" attach="left" box="[317,325,1906,1920]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">2</subScript>
veins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C330CAB17E2BFFEB43C0F829414E1E0F" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E2BFFE943C0F829414A1A85" blockId="8.[151,1437,1563,1987]" box="[199,597,1924,1951]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2BFFE943C0F82942721A84" bold="true" box="[199,365,1924,1950]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Redescription</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2BFFE9427BF82942A61A84" bold="true" box="[380,441,1924,1950]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131185BF7E2BFFE942C0F82941031A85" box="[455,540,1924,1951]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–13" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,211,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-20@9.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 12–13. Schausiana phalerus. 12, ♂ HT: 12a, dorsal view; 12b, ventral view (NHMUK). 13, ♀ (CGCM 24.122): 13a, dorsal view; 13b, ventral view (CGCM). Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413516/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Figs 12</figureCitation>
a–b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E2BFFE943C0F80541BA1AD8" blockId="8.[151,1437,1563,1987]" box="[199,677,1960,1987]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2BFFE943C0F805421B1AD8" box="[199,260,1960,1986]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Head</emphasis>
. Frons ochrish-brown, vertex darker.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF55C9B27E2AFFE84390F95B41F41A2B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413516" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4413516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413516/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" startId="9.[151,264,1782,1806]" targetBox="[162,1425,211,1724]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E2AFFE84390F95B41F41A2B" blockId="9.[151,1436,1782,1842]" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2AFFE84390F95B42521A14" bold="true" box="[151,333,1782,1806]" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">FIGURES 12–13</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AE2B97E2AFFE8425FF95B41341A14" authorityName="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[344,555,1782,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phalerus">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2AFFE8425FF95B41341A14" box="[344,555,1782,1806]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">Schausiana phalerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2AFFE84131F95B41501A14" bold="true" box="[566,591,1782,1806]" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">12</emphasis>
, ♂ HT: 12a, dorsal view; 12b, ventral view (NHMUK). 
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2AFFE84786F95B47851A14" bold="true" box="[1153,1178,1782,1806]" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">13</emphasis>
, ♀ (CGCM 24.122): 13a, dorsal view; 13b, ventral view (CGCM). Scale bar = 1 cm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E2AFFEB43C0F8CD469E1C5B" blockId="9.[151,1436,1888,2023]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E2AFFE843C0F8CD42071A60" box="[199,280,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pro- and mesothorax slightly lighter than vertex, metathorax greyish-brown, ventrally ochrish-brown, metathorax pale yellow. FW length: 
<quantity id="4CD234DF7E2AFFE84129F82941B71A85" box="[558,680,1924,1951]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.75" metricValueMax="6.3" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" unit="mm" value="57.5" valueMax="63.0" valueMin="52.0">52–63 mm</quantity>
, width: 
<quantity id="4CD234DF7E2AFFE84005F82940651A85" box="[770,890,1924,1951]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" unit="mm" value="21.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="20.0">20–23 mm</quantity>
(ratio ~2.7), wingspan: 
<quantity id="4CD234DF7E2AFFE84780F82946021A85" box="[1159,1309,1924,1951]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.215" metricValueMax="1.33" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" unit="mm" value="121.5" valueMax="133.0" valueMin="110.0">110–133 mm</quantity>
; elongated, tornus indistinct; costal margin slightly convex, apex pronounced and acute, outer margin slightly concave from apex to Rs3, inner margin convex. DFW ground colour ochrish-brown with numerous indistinct, transverse thin, dark brown stripes and dots over entire surface; anal area with a single detached black spot; U-shaped band brown, darker posteriorly, not reaching A vein, the proximal arm with a conspicuous silver irregular spot concolorous with the silver and oblique stigma; premarginal and marginal bands barely visible, slightly darker than ground colour; evenly spaced white spine-like specialized scales on the veins. DHW ground colour greyish-brown, costal margin distally brown with some darker spots. VFW and VHW greyish-brown with apex and veins distally dark yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E29FFEB43C0FEE642021CB7" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB43C0FEE6422E1C7F" box="[199,305,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Abdomen</emphasis>
. First two segments dorsally and ventrally concolorous with metathorax, segments III to VIII dorsally black with some dark blue reflecting scales, lighter posteriorly on each segment, ventrally pale yellow as the metathorax.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E29FFEB43C0FE1A47151CC8" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,1034,439,466]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB43C0FE1A42731CCB" box="[199,364,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Not dissected (male 
<typeStatus id="549127987E29FFEB4158FE1A41DE1CCB" box="[607,705,439,465]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="549127987E29FFEB41F0FE1A407D1CCB" box="[759,866,439,465]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">paratypes</typeStatus>
not available).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E29FFEB43C0FE77414C1CEC" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,595,474,502]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB43C0FE77424E1CEE" bold="true" box="[199,337,474,500]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB4267FE7642A81CEF" bold="true" box="[352,439,475,501]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131185BF7E29FFEB42C1FE7641061CEC" box="[454,537,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–13" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,211,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-20@9.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 12–13. Schausiana phalerus. 12, ♂ HT: 12a, dorsal view; 12b, ventral view (NHMUK). 13, ♀ (CGCM 24.122): 13a, dorsal view; 13b, ventral view (CGCM). Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413516/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Figs 13</figureCitation>
a–b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E29FFEB43C0FE5241691F03" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,630,511,537]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB43C0FE52421B1F03" box="[199,260,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Head</emphasis>
. Antenna with ~30 antenomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E29FFEB43C0FD8E420C1F9F" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB43C0FD8E42071F27" box="[199,280,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Thorax</emphasis>
. FW length: 
<quantity id="4CD234DF7E29FFEB42A8FD8F41341F27" box="[431,555,546,573]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" metricValueMax="8.9" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" unit="mm" value="82.0" valueMax="89.0" valueMin="75.0">75–89 mm</quantity>
, width: 
<quantity id="4CD234DF7E29FFEB4180FD8E401E1F27" box="[647,769,547,573]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" unit="mm" value="32.0" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="30.0">30–34 mm</quantity>
(ratio ~2.5), wingspan: 
<quantity id="4CD234DF7E29FFEB4714FD8F47B31F27" box="[1043,1196,546,573]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" unit="mm" value="165.0" valueMax="180.0" valueMin="150.0">150–180 mm</quantity>
. DFW ground colour light brown to yellowish-brown; U-band indistinct, yellow-brown; stigma absent. DHW with apical area concolorous with DFW.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E29FFEB43C0FD2242CF1FB3" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,464,655,681]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB43C0FD22422E1FB3" box="[199,305,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Abdomen</emphasis>
. As for the 
<specimenCount id="9D2C52B37E29FFEB42B3FD2242D31FB3" box="[436,460,655,681]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E29FFEB43C0FD1E412C1FD7" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,563,691,717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB43C0FD1E42991FD7" box="[199,390,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Not dissected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E29FFEB43C0FD7B414E1E0F" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB43C0FD7B42E01FEA" bold="true" box="[199,511,726,752]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Geographical distribution</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AE2B97E29FFEB410AFD7A41E71FEB" authorityName="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[525,760,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phalerus">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB410AFD7A41E71FEB" box="[525,760,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Schausiana phalerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from single localities in the eastern Mexican states of 
<collectingRegion id="49EE57D87E29FFEB43FCFD5642581E0F" box="[251,327,763,789]" country="Mexico" name="Puebla" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Puebla</collectingRegion>
