<subSubSection id="C330CAB17E29FFEB43C0FCB242CC1E23" box="[199,467,799,825]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E29FFEB43C0FCB242CC1E23" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,467,799,825]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB43C0FCB242501E23" bold="true" box="[199,335,799,825]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Host plants</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C330CAB17E29FFEB43C0FCEE463F1E47" box="[199,1312,835,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E29FFEB43C0FCEE463F1E47" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,1312,835,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB43C0FCEE42571E47" bold="true" box="[199,328,835,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Etymology</emphasis>
. It is likely the specific name comes from Greek mythology, son of Alcon from Athens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C330CAB17E29FFEB43C0FCCA42231EF7" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B95993A7E29FFEB43C0FCCA42231EF7" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB43C0FCCA422B1E9B" bold="true" box="[199,308,871,897]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AE2B97E29FFEB4243FCCA412F1E9B" authorityName="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[324,560,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phalerus">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB4243FCCA412F1E9B" box="[324,560,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Schausiana phalerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from three specimens. Although none of the specimens were dissected, the wing ornamentation presents some features that clearly separate this species from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AE2B97E29FFEB461CFC26421B1ED3" authority="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra, 2020" authorityName="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalciope" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB461CFC26421B1ED3" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Schausiana chalciope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26DF8537E29FFEB420DFC02427B1ED3" box="[266,356,943,969]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB420DFC02423B1ED3" bold="true" box="[266,292,943,969]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB4236FC0242421ED3" bold="true" box="[305,349,943,969]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see diagnosis). The presence of specialized scales on the FW of both 
<specimenCount id="9D2C52B37E29FFEB476AFC02479D1ED3" box="[1133,1154,943,969]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D2C52B37E29FFEB47B1FC0247D41ED3" box="[1206,1227,943,969]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
places this species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AE2B97E29FFEB43B3FC7E422A1EF7" authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1949" box="[180,309,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95E45287E29FFEB43B3FC7E422A1EF7" box="[180,309,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Schausiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
